<chapter xml:id="ch-determinants" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Determinants</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
For <m>2\times 2</m> matrices
<me>
A =
\begin{bmatrix}
  a \amp  b \\ c\amp  d
\end{bmatrix}
,
</me>
we saw that <m>A</m> was invertible if and only if its determinant <m>\det(A) = ad-bc</m> was 
nonzero, so the determinant <em>determines</em> whether <m>A</m> is invertible. In this chapter, 
we introduce an <m>n\times n</m> version of the determinant which allows us to check whether 
<m>n\times n</m> matrices are invertible.
</p>
  </introduction>

